@jerrypeng 
> and add RuntimeFactory.close to the JavaInstanceMain.close

Sure, I have added this change to fix the broken thread-runtime for now. and we can add enhancement for caching-client separately.

@cckellogg I could easily create a gke-values.yaml, but I think it would confuse people more than help. For instance, if I include that `nodeSelector: cloud.google.com/gke-nodepool: default-pool`, newcomers might think this is a necessary step to deploy on GKE, which is not. 

The way the chart is after the changes, is completely generic and can be deployed with the values unaltered on any kube cluster. 

Thoughts?
